&lt;/section&gt;&lt;p&gt;Failure by the new corporate parent to provide a parent company guarantee in one of the two prescribed formats may constitute sufficient grounds for the Secretary of State to invoke his powers under the Model Clauses to either order a further change of control or to revoke any UK petroleum licences held by the licensee.&lt;/p&gt;

